==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indium
<hw>In"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Indigo</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare metallic element,
of atomic number 49, discovered in certain ores of zinc, by means of its
characteristic spectrum of two indigo blue lines; hence, its name. In
appearance it resembles zinc, being white or lead gray, soft, malleable
and easily fusible, but in its chemical relation it resembles aluminium
or gallium (valence +3). Symbol In. Atomic weight, 114.82.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

